               <p>THOMAS HALL. On the morning of the 24th of December, about ten minutes to seven o'clock, I took my luggage to the door of <placeName id="t18280110-215-crimeloc1131">the Flower Pot, Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-215-crimeloc1131" type="placeName" value="the Flower Pot, Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-215-crimeloc1131" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-215-off1129 t18280110-215-crimeloc1131"></join> - I stopped to speak to the guard of the Telegraph coach, and my coat was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-215-person1284">
                  WILLIAM 
                  LARKE
               <interp inst="t18280110-215-person1284" type="surname" value="LARKE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-215-person1284" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-215-person1284" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Mr. Hall, assisting him with his luggage; his great coat was by the door - I saw the prisoner come and take it up; he and another, who was with him, walked on - I followed them, and heard his companion say, "Drop it! Drop it!" he did so - I took it up, and secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-215-person1285">
                  WILLIAM 
                  RIXLEY
